    "updated_at": "2016-06-02T23:14:39Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "In release 0.14, fail-fast became the default behavior for all wrapped languages (gRPC-Go will follow suit):\nhttps://github.com/grpc/grpc/releases\n\nWith fail-fast, attempting to connect to an unavailable server will throw an exception immediately.\n\nWe plan on exposing the ability to disable fail-fast mode in the wrapped language APIs, but in the mean time, clients should handle unavailable server exceptions.  \n\nIn gRPC-Python, there is an open issue where unhandled exceptions cause the client to freeze:\nhttps://github.com/grpc/grpc/issues/6666\n\nWhich causes the issue seen here.\n"
  },
